  <title>POP-Sketch-Element-Spline</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Sketch-Element<keyword>Spline</keyword></keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Popup Box"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="width:453px; cell-padding:1px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:164px;">
          <para styleclass="Image Caption"><image src="MD--Pop-Sketch-Element-Spline.png" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Open and Closed Splines]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:268px;">
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal;">A </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> is a <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Sketch-Elements">sketch-element</link>. It is defined by the position, gradient, curvature of constraint points along the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> shape.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> can be open<image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> or closed<image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">If you click a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Spline</text> one time, then the drag-handles <image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> show You can drag the arrow-heads to control the gradient and the curvature of the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">spline</text> at the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">You can drag the handles in the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Mechanism-Editor</text> and <text styleclass="Popup Box2">Part-Editors</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#343400;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-FunctionBlock-BlendCurve">Blend-Curve</link>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
